They have to have a  location for the food and services of the homeless that is out of the downtown core....as well as accommodations.  Perhaps, a community could be built and situated on the land behind Lion's Park to make a multiplex design in a  warehouse type build and accommodating homeless  families, individual areas for single men and women. This build could include meal services, physical and mental help services, as well as support staff 24/7 and on the job training for individuals. People would have the HOPE  to be able to get back to living  a normal life once again.
The existing homeless situation is plaguing all cities and towns....like 'a dog chasing his tail'. Perhaps, if a group of people established a working model in one small city, over a period of 5 years the kinks could be outed;
success for other centres on the horizon.

